'''罗伯特·尼珀德'''（{{lang-de|Robert Nippoldt}}，{{bd|1977年}}），生于[[德国|德国]][[克拉嫩堡|克拉嫩堡]]，是一名德国籍[[插画家|插画家]]、平面设计师和图画作家<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.taschen.com/pages/en/community/video/37407.robert_nippoldt_the_book_artist.htm |title=Robert Nippoldt – The Book Artist |accessdate=2015-04-23 |archive-date=2014-11-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141103185201/http://www.taschen.com/pages/en/community/video/37407.robert_nippoldt_the_book_artist.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。
曾在明斯特的应用科技大学攻读平面设计和插画专业。图书《黑帮之王》即为他的毕业设计作品。两年之后（2007年），他出版了自己的第二本图书《爵士乐：咆哮的二十年代的纽约》<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://en.vogue.fr/fashion-culture/fashion-books/diaporama/fitzgerald-flashback-great-gatsby-jazz-age-new-york-book/12971 |title=“Jazz.New York in the Roaring Twenties” at VOGUE |accessdate=2015-04-23 |archive-date=2016-11-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161113045049/http://en.vogue.fr/fashion-culture/fashion-books/diaporama/fitzgerald-flashback-great-gatsby-jazz-age-new-york-book/12971 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.eslite.com/product.aspx?pgid=1002167382228256 |title=“Jazz” on Eslite |access-date=2015-04-23 |archive-date=2018-09-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180905180155/http://www.eslite.com/product.aspx?pgid=1002167382228256 |dead-url=no }}</ref> 。该书被译成了多种语言，并为他赢得了无数奖项。在2010年，他的第三部作品《重回好莱坞30年代》<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/photos/2014/11/hollywood-1930s-illustrations |title=“Hollywood in the 1930s” at Vanity Fair |accessdate=2015-04-23 |archive-date=2017-06-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170619043039/http://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/photos/2014/11/hollywood-1930s-illustrations |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.gq-magazine.co.uk/entertainment/articles/2014-11/14/hollywood-in-the-30s-gallery-taschen |title=Review of the book “Hollywood” at GQ Magazine |accessdate=2015-04-23 |archive-date=2015-11-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151121042100/http://www.gq-magazine.co.uk/entertainment/articles/2014-11/14/hollywood-in-the-30s-gallery-taschen |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://m.jiemian.com/article/210891.html |title=“Hollywood” at Jiemian |access-date=2015-04-23 |archive-date=2018-09-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180905223300/https://m.jiemian.com/article/210891.html |dead-url=no }}</ref> 面世，书中刻画了二十世纪20年代和30年代下的美国好莱坞。2017年，他的第四本图书《夜幕降临咆哮的二十年代的柏林》由塔森出版社出版。他的图书往往随附游戏<ref>[http://mayfairgames.com/game.php?id=8“Gangster” board game at Myfair Games]{{dead link|date=2018年4月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> 和限量版的丝网版画<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://nippoldt.de/en/silkscreens |title=Silkscreens by Robert Nippoldt |accessdate=2015-04-23 |archive-date=2015-04-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150404115501/http://nippoldt.de/en/silkscreens |dead-url=no }}</ref>。除了图书作品外，他还为某些国际杂志和客户绘制插画，如《[[纽约客|纽约客]]》<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2013/11/25/roman-conquests |title=“The Great Beauty”, illustration by Robert Nippoldt for The New Yorker |accessdate=2015-04-23 |archive-date=2017-11-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171114093536/https://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2013/11/25/roman-conquests |dead-url=no }}</ref>、《[[法国世界报|法国世界报]]》、《[[时代周报|时代周报]]》、《[[梅赛德斯-奔驰|梅赛德斯-奔驰]]》杂志、《[[读者文摘|读者文摘]]》<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.readersdigest.co.uk/inspire/life-skills/becoming-jazz-singer-my-30s |title=“Becoming a jazz singer in my 30s”, illustration by Robert Nippoldt for Reader’s Digest |accessdate=2015-04-23 |archive-date=2015-03-17 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20150317112945/http://www.readersdigest.co.uk/inspire/life-skills/becoming-jazz-singer-my-30s |dead-url=yes }}</ref>、[[塔森出版社|塔森出版社]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.taschen.com/pages/en/search/result.1.htm?show_all=catalogue&search_string=nippoldt |title=Robert Nippoldt at TASCHEN |accessdate=2015-04-23 |archive-date=2015-04-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402143735/http://www.taschen.com/pages/en/search/result.1.htm?show_all=catalogue&search_string=nippoldt |dead-url=no }}</ref>和《[[时代杂志|时代杂志]]》。
在与姐姐阿斯特丽德·尼珀德和妻子克里丝汀娜·尼珀德的一同努力下，罗伯特成立了“尼珀德工作室”，并将其纳入为自身品牌之一<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://studionippoldt.de/en/ |title=Studio Nippoldt |accessdate=2015-04-23 |archive-date=2015-04-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150406150336/http://www.studionippoldt.de/en/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2014/03/31/change-agents |title=“The Americans”, illustration by Studio Nippoldt for The New Yorker |accessdate=2015-04-23 |archive-date=2018-01-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180118075657/https://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2014/03/31/change-agents |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

“Ein Rätselhafter Schimmer”是由《柏林》一书衍生的演出，由罗伯特·尼珀德和“Trio Größenwahn”在 2015-2018 年间创作。该舞台表演包含现场绘画和现场音乐，已演出超过 50 场，还曾经在波恩 Pantheon 剧院、柏林 Heimathafen 剧院和爱达邮轮上演出。

德国、瑞士和西班牙举办的展会均有展出过罗伯特·尼珀德的作品。他的工作室位于明斯特的一所老旧货物仓库中。

